<br>
PvP BLOWS since the patch.  I'm a carbineer, not a BH carbineer either, just the normal kind.  And I was never very useful in PvP despite the fact that I have crippleshot and chargeshot and a 400+dmg carbine.  Now after the patch, I'm useless.  My once semi-decent crippleshot now does about 50 dmg per hit.  It takes me so long to kill someone if it's 1 on 1, and if they have stims you can just forget about it.  I was duking it out with 1 guy for like 6 minutes till we ran out of stims and I managed to knock him down and land a hit in the action pool just as he bled.<br>
Commandos burning me still blows, I'm getting incapped after 2 burns and can rarely make it to water even when it's 50m away.  Poison is still invincible, nothing I can do about that since practically no one can heal it and it incaps my mind in two hits.<br>
Just a bit earlier today a master doc (may have been CM too but had the doc title on) was running around theed.  After he buffed himself he was invincible!  Even with 4 guys shooting him we could never do enough dmg to drain his health and he just kept stimming himself back to full health while he ran around chucking area poison at us.<br>
Then a bit later a few commandos were running around with a doc and no matter what we tried they just kept lighting us on fire and acting like they were actually good.  Im close to master CH and a bit past half way to master carbineer and a lousy commando with his damned flamethrower and the flamethrower 1 box was killing me.  They even burned my Hanadak Drifter who has 80% heat resists (apparently nothing can help him resist the burns, just the actual hit).<br>
And to top it off, they just shot more fire at 2 of the other guy's gurreck, mountain dewback, and mature hanadak rock smasher.<br>
<br>
If they don't fix PvP, I'm quitting the game.  Whenever I got bored (which is pretty often), I would go find some people to fight.  But now that the few, the proud, the over-powered @#%$ heads can run everything because my gun is so stunted I'm a chuba to them while they still incap me in 2 hits I'm giving it up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tona@creaturehandlersofswg>Tona</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#70DB93>(10/15/03 2:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The New Patch In General</span><hr size=1> My biggest complaint about the newest big patch is about creature training.  Every day, when I log in, I have to retrain all the pets I've tamed since the patch.  The older ones are fine and don't lose their training and I get the XP for training the younger ones again, but it's a pain in the arse to have to retrain 4 -5 pets every day. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=9.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=9.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub60.ezboa